    "body": "\"+yy## Problem\r\n\r\nIntro text and styling were hard-coded in C, which made it difficult to override and also kept layout tied to a fixed line count.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\nMove intro content generation into Lua while keeping rendering in C, validate the returned chunk structure, center based on the actual line count, and show an `ErrorMsg`-highlighted fallback when loading fails. Add functional coverage for Lua overrides and failure handling.\r\n\r\nAI-assisted: OpenCode\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Custom Lua intro example</summary>\r\n\r\n![Custom Lua intro](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/fc764715-f746-4008-aee8-ada8310d3068)\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nvim.cmd([[highlight IntroGlow guifg=#ffd7ff guibg=#5f00af gui=bold,italic]])\r\n\r\nrequire('vim._core.intro').display = function()\r\n  local v = vim.version()\r\n\r\n  return {\r\n    {\r\n      { '╭═', 'Special' },\r\n      { ' LOUD LUA INTRO ', 'Title' },\r\n      { '═╮', 'Special' },\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      { '│ ', 'Special' },\r\n      { ('Neovim %d.%d.%d'):format(v.major, v.minor, v.patch), 'String' },\r\n      { ' │', 'Special' },\r\n    },\r\n    { { '╰══════════════════╯', 'Special' } },\r\n    {},\r\n    {\r\n      { 'Everything on this screen came from ', 'Comment' },\r\n      { 'vim._intro()', 'Identifier' },\r\n    },\r\n    { { 'Chunks can mix colors and styles inline.', 'Statement' } },\r\n    {},\r\n    {\r\n      { 'run  ', 'Comment' },\r\n      { ':', 'ErrorMsg' },\r\n      { 'help', 'Function' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'WarningMsg' },\r\n      { ' for help', 'Question' },\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      { 'run  ', 'Comment' },\r\n      { ':', 'ErrorMsg' },\r\n      { 'checkhealth', 'Statement' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'WarningMsg' },\r\n      { ' to inspect your setup', 'MoreMsg' },\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      { 'run  ', 'Comment' },\r\n      { ':', 'ErrorMsg' },\r\n      { 'qa', 'Type' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'WarningMsg' },\r\n      { ' to quit all windows', 'Directory' },\r\n    },\r\n    {},\r\n    { { 'Built entirely from builtin highlight groups.', 'IntroGlow' } },\r\n  }\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Override matching the old default intro style</summary>\r\n\r\n![Old Default-style Lua intro override](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7e7670ec-9b8d-473a-b58c-4ac4140ccc0a)\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nrequire('vim._core.intro').display = function()\r\n  local v = vim.version()\r\n\r\n  return {\r\n    { { 'NVIM ' .. tostring(v) } },\r\n    {},\r\n    { { 'Nvim is open source and freely distributable' } },\r\n    { { 'https://neovim.io/#chat' } },\r\n    {},\r\n    {\r\n      { 'type  :help nvim' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'SpecialKey' },\r\n      { '       if you are new! ' },\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      { 'type  :checkhealth' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'SpecialKey' },\r\n      { '     to optimize Nvim' },\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      { 'type  :q' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'SpecialKey' },\r\n      { '               to exit         ' },\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      { 'type  :help' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'SpecialKey' },\r\n      { '            for help        ' },\r\n    },\r\n    {},\r\n    {\r\n      { 'type  :help news' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'SpecialKey' },\r\n      { (' to see changes in v%d.%d'):format(v.major, v.minor) },\r\n    },\r\n    {},\r\n    { { 'Help poor children in Uganda!' } },\r\n    {\r\n      { 'type  :help Kuwasha' },\r\n      { '<Enter>', 'SpecialKey' },\r\n      { '    for information ' },\r\n    },\r\n  }\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary>Failure handling example</summary>\r\n\r\n![Failure handling intro fallback](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e9485738-952f-41db-904f-b3e76cca62ef)\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nrequire('vim._core.intro').display = function()\r\n  error('intentional intro failure')\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>",
